Companion (bottom-screen merchant repair) — export + control bridge for the native
MerchantRepair window (GM_MerchantRepair). Mirrors companion-barter-export.patch, but
much simpler (a static damaged-item list + one-shot repair actions, no offer/balance
state).

Outbound (COMPANION_REPAIR_*, streamed one small line each for 4096-byte flush safety),
emitted from MerchantRepair::setPtr → companionExportOpen(): OPEN:<npcName> →
COMPANION_PLAYER_GOLD:<amount> → ITEM:<name>|<sid>|<condition>|<maxCondition>|<repairCost>*
→ END. sid is the item's ordinal index in the exported (alphabetically sorted) damaged
list — a stable handle because GM_MerchantRepair pauses the sim, so the set only changes
on a repair (which re-exports fresh indices). CLOSED on close.

Inbound: a file-static gCompanionMerchantRepair (set in the ctor) plus three extern "C"
bridges — companionRepairItem/companionRepairAll/companionRepairCancel — let
drainCompanionCommands drive repair from CMP:repair_* commands. companionRepairByIndex and
companionRepairAll mirror the native onRepairButtonClick (full setCharge restore, restack,
deduct player gold, credit the NPC gold pool, play the Repair sound) and re-export after
each repair. Prices come from MechanicsManager::getBarterOffer (native-only — the reason
this must be a native bridge, same as barter). Each bridge no-ops unless
containsMode(GM_MerchantRepair) (stale-window guard).

Close signal: the native window is HIDDEN the moment the mode opens in DS mode
(companion-hide-gamewindows-on-dsmode.patch), so the usual visible->hidden onClose()
transition never fires. COMPANION_REPAIR_CLOSED is therefore emitted explicitly, once-
guarded (gCompanionRepairSessionOpen), from every close path: the companionRepairCancel
bridge (bottom-screen Cancel), exit() (B/Escape), and onOkButtonClick (native OK, Vanilla).
